---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../content/site.js";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Closed-beta privacy summary for CategoryFix, aligned with the current Shopify app implementation."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy wording should stay as narrow as the product behavior.</h1>
    <p>
      This privacy summary is tailored to the current closed beta. It describes the data handling
      implied by the present repository and should be reviewed again before broader launch.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="legal-panel">
    <section>
      <h2>What the app uses</h2>
      <p>
        CategoryFix connects to Shopify so it can read product information needed to detect missing
        or likely-wrong product categories and, when a merchant confirms changes, write approved
        category updates back to Shopify.
      </p>
      <p>
        Current product behavior includes scan records, recommendation findings, apply jobs,
        rollback jobs, audit events, and webhook processing data needed to keep the workflow
        explainable and reversible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why the data is used</h2>
      <p>
        The app uses Shopify product fields such as title, product type, vendor, tags, collections,
        and existing category state to generate reviewable category recommendations. It also stores
        operational records so merchants can inspect what changed and roll back approved writes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>AI-assisted fallback</h2>
      <p>
        AI assistance is optional in the current product. When enabled, it is intended only for
        deterministic no-safe outcomes and is presented as advisory support rather than definitive
        platform truth.
      </p>
      <p>
        CategoryFix does not autonomously apply AI-only category updates. Merchant review remains
        required before any category write occurs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Because this beta may evolve before wider release, any final production privacy policy
        should confirm the exact model configuration, data flow, and retention details in use at
        that time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Support and deletion requests</h2>
      <p>
        CategoryFix implements Shopify compliance webhook handling and expects published privacy
        behavior to stay consistent with those flows. Questions about beta privacy handling can be
        sent to <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.supportEmail}`}>{siteConfig.supportEmail}</a>.
      </p>
      <p>No live billing is enabled in the current closed beta.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
